systems and download files.  I then reboot to Linux and
mount the DOS partition and copy the files into Linux
directory space.

Wouldn't it be neat if you could simply launch linux
by typing in a DOS command line?  Save the trouble of
rebooting every time?

Better yet, is there a version of minicom or something that
works without having to reset the screen each time it
